WEBVTT

00:00.959 --> 00:05.417
♪♪

00:05.417 --> 00:07.834
("Jingle Bells")

00:07.834 --> 00:09.792
♪♪

00:09.792 --> 00:10.917
JEN: Hey, do you think
the Lyft driver

00:10.917 --> 00:13.208
-could tell we were drunk?
-Well, not the Lyft driver,

00:13.208 --> 00:16.625
but maybe the driver
of the first car you got into.

00:16.625 --> 00:17.625
Hey, guys.

00:17.625 --> 00:20.000
JEN:
Oh, hi, Amanda.

00:20.000 --> 00:23.041
-Hey, how did Lark do?
-Great--we played outside.

00:23.041 --> 00:24.709
Until that guy with
the shopping cart walked by.

00:24.709 --> 00:26.417
Oh, yeah,
that's a good call.

00:26.417 --> 00:27.375
You're not going to
believe this,

00:27.375 --> 00:29.542
but he's not actually
going shopping.

00:29.542 --> 00:31.458
GREG: Hey, I'm going to get
out of these clothes.

00:31.458 --> 00:34.333
All right? Put on some tunes,
maybe fire up a scented candle?

00:34.333 --> 00:35.333
I'm into it, I'm into it,
I'm into it.

00:35.333 --> 00:36.625
Thank you!

00:36.625 --> 00:38.041
Uh, here, let me
write you a check.

00:38.041 --> 00:39.333
Thanks, Jen.

00:39.333 --> 00:41.291
I love those shoes.

00:41.291 --> 00:42.333
Thank you.

00:42.333 --> 00:43.417
Hey, you can borrow them

00:43.417 --> 00:44.709
for your sister's wedding
if you want.

00:44.709 --> 00:46.083
She called it off.

00:46.083 --> 00:47.375
What?

00:47.375 --> 00:48.667
(gasps) I knew it.

00:48.667 --> 00:50.333
What was it, secret family?

00:50.333 --> 00:52.583
Secret boyfriend--and not hers.

00:52.583 --> 00:54.208
Well, you know what I say.

00:54.208 --> 00:56.750
Never trust a man with Botox.

00:56.750 --> 00:58.333
Unless he's giving you Botox.

00:58.333 --> 01:00.333
♪♪

01:00.333 --> 01:02.250
Honey, you coming to bed?

01:02.250 --> 01:04.041
JEN: I guess that's why
you should never get

01:04.041 --> 01:05.250
your vows tattooed
on your lower back.

01:05.250 --> 01:06.291
-(laughs)
-Zing!

01:06.291 --> 01:08.125
(laughing flatly)

01:08.125 --> 01:09.625
GREG:
You guys, uh,

01:09.625 --> 01:10.583
you good?

01:10.583 --> 01:11.917
-Yeah.
-Yeah.

01:11.917 --> 01:13.709
Well, I'm, uh...

01:13.709 --> 01:15.583
I'm going to go
put in my retainer and...

01:15.583 --> 01:16.583
go to bed.

01:16.583 --> 01:17.917
Okay, honey, love you.

01:17.917 --> 01:19.000
Love you.

01:19.000 --> 01:20.542
AMANDA: Bye!
JEN: Night-night.

01:21.709 --> 01:23.125
Those are his special jammies.

01:23.125 --> 01:25.500
♪♪

01:25.500 --> 01:27.083
It's like this every time.

01:27.083 --> 01:28.792
Jen and I come back
from a night out

01:28.792 --> 01:29.709
with a little buzz.

01:29.709 --> 01:32.000
Things start getting
a little hot, and then...

01:32.000 --> 01:33.917
Start picturing your mom
and it's over.

01:33.917 --> 01:35.583
What? No.

01:35.583 --> 01:37.333
Jen starts talking
to our babysitter.

01:37.333 --> 01:39.125
Next thing I know,
it's two hours later.

01:39.125 --> 01:41.542
They've opened up a bottle
of wine, started chatting,

01:41.542 --> 01:44.333
and I'm sitting there in
my silk pajamas for nothing.

01:44.333 --> 01:46.375
You know, and those things
got to get dry cleaned.

01:46.375 --> 01:48.375
Your sex window closed.

01:48.375 --> 01:49.542
-Sex window?
-Yeah, you know,

01:49.542 --> 01:50.709
when you start having kids,

01:50.709 --> 01:53.083
you got a very small amount
of time to have sex.

01:53.083 --> 01:55.125
It's usually right after
the kids go to sleep

01:55.125 --> 01:57.667
and before you're so exhausted
that you fall asleep.

01:57.667 --> 02:01.000
Yes! My babysitter's
killed my sex window.

02:01.000 --> 02:02.291
Tell you what you need to do.

02:02.291 --> 02:03.542
Next time you want to go out,
you hire Samantha.

02:03.542 --> 02:05.333
She won't stick around
and chat with Jen.

02:05.333 --> 02:07.458
Teenagers do not like
talking to adults.

02:07.458 --> 02:09.041
That is a fantastic idea.

02:09.041 --> 02:10.250
Yeah, and I'll drop her off
and pick her up;

02:10.250 --> 02:11.917
that way you'll know
she'll leave right away

02:11.917 --> 02:13.333
and your sex window stays open.

02:13.333 --> 02:15.875
Just make sure you close it
before Mom sneaks in.

02:15.875 --> 02:18.917
Okay, wait, are you talking
about your mom or my mom?

02:20.166 --> 02:22.083
Whichever one's not weird.

02:22.083 --> 02:23.625
(tape rips)

02:23.625 --> 02:26.458
♪♪

02:26.458 --> 02:27.875
JEN: I know we say it
every year, but can this be

02:27.875 --> 02:30.417
the last year
we go to the ugly sweater party?

02:30.417 --> 02:32.875
I cannot wait
to take this thing off.

02:32.875 --> 02:34.208
GREG:
Well, I cannot wait

02:34.208 --> 02:35.917
to take it off of you.

02:35.917 --> 02:38.250
TIM (slurring): Hey, you
guys are 45 minutes late.

02:38.250 --> 02:39.500
JEN:
Oh, yeah, sorry.

02:39.500 --> 02:42.375
We ran into these friends
we hadn't seen in forever.

02:42.375 --> 02:43.917
Oh, yeah, do I know them?
Were they at the wedding?

02:43.917 --> 02:45.834
Was it the couple
with the turtles?

02:45.834 --> 02:47.583
Doesn't matter--
who cares, right?

02:47.583 --> 02:49.041
It's time to get Sam home,
right?

02:49.041 --> 02:50.041
Bedtime.

02:50.041 --> 02:52.709
TIM (chuckles):
I can't drive right now.

02:52.709 --> 02:53.875
I'm sorry, what?

02:53.875 --> 02:55.166
You guys weren't here,
so I started drinking.

02:55.166 --> 02:57.959
What else am I supposed to do
to pass the time?

02:57.959 --> 03:00.333
Uh, I don't know,
uh, talk to Sam?

03:00.333 --> 03:01.709
I don't like talking to adults.

03:01.709 --> 03:03.834
All right, well, I'm
going to let you guys work out

03:03.834 --> 03:06.333
whatever this is, and I'm
going to hop into my cozies.

03:06.333 --> 03:10.750
No--no, no, no, no, no,
no, no cozies!

03:10.750 --> 03:12.583
-Tim!
-Yeah, bro.

03:12.583 --> 03:16.959
-Can I talk to you for a second?
-Uh-oh, sounds like last call.

03:16.959 --> 03:19.417
You don't have to go home,
but you can't stay here.

03:21.500 --> 03:24.166
Why would you start drinking if
you knew you had to drive home?

03:24.166 --> 03:26.000
Hey, not my fault
you were late.

03:26.000 --> 03:29.166
Besides, I was still
feeling that glow.

03:29.166 --> 03:30.709
What glow?

03:30.709 --> 03:32.291
Well, you know,
all the kids were out,

03:32.291 --> 03:35.083
so Heather and I had ourselves
a good little time

03:35.083 --> 03:36.834
with the house
all to ourselves.

03:36.834 --> 03:39.458
That's why you offered up
Sam to babysit.

03:39.458 --> 03:40.375
Mm.

03:40.375 --> 03:42.834
You created your own sex window
and you traded it for mine.

03:42.834 --> 03:45.125
Had to. You know...

03:45.125 --> 03:46.458
it's hard to get
that window open.

03:46.458 --> 03:49.333
It's been painted shut with
years of children and pets

03:49.333 --> 03:51.041
and intermittent
weight gain.

03:51.041 --> 03:52.625
Yeah, well, that's
your problem, not mine.

03:52.625 --> 03:53.750
Come on,
we're getting in the car.

03:53.750 --> 03:55.250
Let's go, come on!

03:55.250 --> 03:57.166
Sam, come on,
taking you home.

03:57.166 --> 03:59.166
Come on, chop-chop.

03:59.166 --> 04:01.792
(metal crunching)

04:01.792 --> 04:03.291
All right!

04:03.291 --> 04:05.667
You're home; now get out.

04:05.667 --> 04:07.375
Sam?

04:07.375 --> 04:08.750
Honey, thank you.

04:10.208 --> 04:12.458
You ran over my bike!

04:12.458 --> 04:14.083
GREG: Oh, come on,
like you ever use it.

04:14.083 --> 04:15.250
SAM:
Oh, I forgot to tell you.

04:15.250 --> 04:17.250
I think Lark may be
allergic to...

04:17.250 --> 04:18.834
Yeah, yeah,
she's a baby.

04:18.834 --> 04:20.959
She's doing new stuff
all the time.

04:23.458 --> 04:25.458
He's right,
I never ride that thing.

04:25.458 --> 04:27.333
♪♪

04:27.333 --> 04:28.083
Ta-da! No.

04:30.000 --> 04:33.667
No, no, no, no, no, no,
no, no, no, no, no, Jen.

04:33.667 --> 04:35.750
(softly): Jen, wake up,
don't close the window.

04:35.750 --> 04:37.250
Wake up, wake up,
wake up!

04:37.250 --> 04:38.875
-Huh? Oh, my God.
-Hi.

04:38.875 --> 04:40.542
-Hi.
-Hi. I'm so sorry.

04:40.542 --> 04:41.750
I fell asleep.

04:41.750 --> 04:43.291
It's okay, because, look.

04:43.291 --> 04:45.500
You're up now, so...

04:45.500 --> 04:47.250
-Yeah.
-Hi.

04:57.208 --> 04:59.125
Okay.

04:59.125 --> 05:00.583
All right, you know what?

05:00.583 --> 05:02.375
Let's, um, let's just
set an early alarm

05:02.375 --> 05:04.792
and we can, we can try
again in the morning.

05:04.792 --> 05:06.041
Oh, that's a great idea.

05:06.041 --> 05:07.667
Yeah, that's way better
than doing it tonight.

05:07.667 --> 05:10.291
-Eh...
-Okay, I love you.

05:10.291 --> 05:12.375
-Love you, too.
-Okay.

05:15.041 --> 05:17.959
♪♪

05:17.959 --> 05:20.667
(phone alarm chiming)

05:24.959 --> 05:26.458
Yeah, right.

05:28.500 --> 05:30.208
(alarm stops)

05:30.208 --> 05:35.500
♪♪

05:35.500 --> 05:37.333
I love my new vanity.

05:37.333 --> 05:39.291
JOHN: I'm sorry I couldn't keep
a secret till Christmas,

05:39.291 --> 05:41.542
but I just got too excited.

05:41.542 --> 05:43.417
Will you have it built
before my sleepover tonight?

05:43.417 --> 05:45.166
-Oh, yeah.
-I promised makeovers,

05:45.166 --> 05:47.834
and some of my friends are
in desperate need.

05:47.834 --> 05:49.000
JOHN: Well, that shouldn't be
a problem

05:49.000 --> 05:50.792
unless your Uncle Matt
holds me up.

05:50.792 --> 05:52.709
What...You begged me
to help.

05:52.709 --> 05:54.542
Well, Greg has
his Ultimate Frisbee game

05:54.542 --> 05:57.709
and Tim is hung over,
so here we are.

05:57.709 --> 06:01.458
Hey, Dad, how many, uh, fluber
rods are we supposed to have?

06:01.458 --> 06:03.834
Well, I don't know about
you, but I just got the one.

06:03.834 --> 06:05.083
-(giggles)
-No.

06:05.083 --> 06:06.166
Huh?

06:06.166 --> 06:07.291
These things--
how many of these

06:07.291 --> 06:09.500
do the instructions
say we're supposed to have?

06:09.500 --> 06:11.875
-This is the instructions?
-Yeah.

06:11.875 --> 06:13.542
Oh, I don't know
what country this is from,

06:13.542 --> 06:17.250
but I guarantee you
they couldn't beat us in a war.

06:17.250 --> 06:18.542
Whoa, what are you doing?!

06:18.542 --> 06:20.458
Unless the instructions say
to tear up the instructions,

06:20.458 --> 06:22.417
that's really stupid.

06:22.417 --> 06:24.250
There's a picture right
here of the finished product,

06:24.250 --> 06:26.750
and that's a lot more than
Frank Lloyd Webber ever had.

06:26.750 --> 06:28.542
And he did okay.

06:28.542 --> 06:30.750
Right, but he had blueprints
and a different name.

06:30.750 --> 06:32.083
Well, excuse me.

06:32.083 --> 06:34.542
Sir Frank Lloyd Webber,
good for him.

06:34.542 --> 06:39.041
♪♪

06:39.041 --> 06:43.542
Hmm, something must be wrong
with the picture from the box.

06:43.542 --> 06:45.458
Okay, uh, let's just go online

06:45.458 --> 06:48.500
and find an instructional video.

06:48.500 --> 06:50.959
The wiffy password's
"seven," big "S."

06:53.417 --> 06:55.542
Now, just so I'm clear,

06:55.542 --> 06:58.041
that little girl thinks
her daddy's in Iraq

06:58.041 --> 07:01.375
and he's really hiding in a
cardboard box in her school gym?

07:01.375 --> 07:03.208
Yeah, just watch her face
when she sees him

07:03.208 --> 07:04.583
for the first time.

07:04.583 --> 07:07.208
Oh, makes me
want to re-enlist.

07:07.208 --> 07:08.792
Wait, wait, wait.

07:08.792 --> 07:11.291
Wait till you see the one
about the police dog

07:11.291 --> 07:13.750
that has to be euthanized and is
walking past a line of officers.

07:15.458 --> 07:17.291
(somber music plays over laptop)

07:17.291 --> 07:18.917
Don't look at me;

07:18.917 --> 07:20.792
you don't want to see
your old man cry.

07:20.792 --> 07:23.333
Oh, my God.
You guys are watching videos?

07:23.333 --> 07:25.166
Sophia's friends are
going to be here in an hour

07:25.166 --> 07:26.834
and that little Mallory
needs a makeover.

07:26.834 --> 07:28.667
Her bangs are so stale.

07:28.667 --> 07:30.667
Okay, okay, all right.

07:30.667 --> 07:32.583
-Let's focus, huh?
JOHN: Yeah.

07:32.583 --> 07:34.500
I think that this could help us.

07:34.500 --> 07:37.875
<i>Hi, guys! Today we are going</i>
<i>to be putting together a vanity</i>

07:37.875 --> 07:40.125
<i>so I can look in it</i>
<i>and see how ugly I am.</i>

07:40.125 --> 07:41.250
<i>Just kidding!</i>

07:41.250 --> 07:42.917
<i>Comment below how pretty</i>
<i>you think I am.</i>

07:42.917 --> 07:45.542
<i>The best compliment</i>
<i>is going to get a shout-out.</i>

07:45.542 --> 07:48.250
20 million people
have watched this.

07:48.250 --> 07:49.709
I-I want a shout-out.

07:49.709 --> 07:51.750
Okay, wait, wait, wait.
Can we please just follow

07:51.750 --> 07:53.291
her instructions
and finish this?

07:53.291 --> 07:55.458
Why don't you follow
my instructions, huh?

07:55.458 --> 07:57.125
Go to my garage,

07:57.125 --> 08:00.250
grab a handful of 100 regular
wood screws and my power drill.

08:00.250 --> 08:01.625
Fine.

08:01.625 --> 08:03.500
But don't you watch any
sad videos without me.

08:03.500 --> 08:06.375
I saw you eyeing the one about
unlikely animal friendships.

08:09.667 --> 08:10.750
Don't!

08:10.750 --> 08:13.500
♪♪

08:13.500 --> 08:16.125
All right, I think
we got ourselves a vanity.

08:16.125 --> 08:17.875
You want to give it
a test drive, Soph,

08:17.875 --> 08:19.083
or wait for your ugly friends?

08:19.083 --> 08:20.583
-I'm going to try it.
-All right.

08:24.083 --> 08:25.166
I'm giving you guys

08:25.166 --> 08:27.333
-one star on Yelp.
-Oh, we don't need handles.

08:27.333 --> 08:29.959
It just takes you longer
to get to your rouge.

08:34.667 --> 08:37.166
W-We don't need mirrors.

08:37.166 --> 08:39.959
It just encourages vanity...

08:39.959 --> 08:42.125
Merry Christmas, Soph.

08:42.125 --> 08:45.417
Is this a joke so I'll
appreciate the real gift?

08:45.417 --> 08:48.125
Uh, yeah!

08:48.125 --> 08:49.709
There's no way
we can fix this.

08:49.709 --> 08:51.166
This is why we shouldn't
have used wood screws.

08:51.166 --> 08:52.583
Why didn't you say something?

08:52.583 --> 08:54.458
I've been following your lead.

08:54.458 --> 08:56.458
Why couldn't we have just
followed the instructions?

08:56.458 --> 08:57.875
Why'd you even ask for my help

08:57.875 --> 09:00.625
if you weren't going to listen
to a word that I say?

09:00.625 --> 09:01.875
Hmm.

09:01.875 --> 09:03.500
(zipper whooshes)

09:03.500 --> 09:05.208
I miss hanging out with you.

09:06.959 --> 09:08.208
Really?

09:08.208 --> 09:10.417
Well, you moved
out of the garage,

09:10.417 --> 09:11.750
and I miss having a buddy.

09:13.083 --> 09:14.709
Greg may be our favorite,

09:14.709 --> 09:17.291
but you're the one
I got used to having around.

09:19.417 --> 09:21.250
Uncle Matt, are you crying?

09:21.250 --> 09:23.250
No, it's this damn
police dog video.

09:23.250 --> 09:24.583
Poor fella.

09:24.583 --> 09:26.166
Yeah, he could sniff out a bomb,

09:26.166 --> 09:28.917
but, uh, couldn't sniff out
his own cancer.

09:28.917 --> 09:31.875
SOPHIA: Guys, I know you're
having a moment,

09:31.875 --> 09:35.208
but my friends
will be here any minute,

09:35.208 --> 09:36.959
and I promised them a spectacle.

09:36.959 --> 09:39.917
♪♪

09:39.917 --> 09:41.917
Thank you so much.

09:41.917 --> 09:44.083
Who needs a vanity for makeovers

09:44.083 --> 09:46.542
when everyone looks good
in this light?

09:46.542 --> 09:49.750
(whispers):
Even Mallory.

09:49.750 --> 09:52.125
Well, may not have been
exactly what we set out to do,

09:52.125 --> 09:55.667
but we made one little girl
very happy this Christmas.

09:55.667 --> 09:57.333
We sure did.

09:57.333 --> 09:59.875
I wish Greg was here.

09:59.875 --> 10:01.542
(flatly):
Thanks, Dad.

10:01.542 --> 10:03.333
Oh, you know who would
really love this?

10:03.333 --> 10:04.834
Don't say Greg.

10:04.834 --> 10:05.792
Okay.

10:05.792 --> 10:07.375
Let's just watch the fire.

10:07.375 --> 10:13.291
♪♪

10:13.291 --> 10:14.709
CHRIS:
Let's try on some dresses!

10:14.709 --> 10:15.667
(cheering)

10:15.667 --> 10:17.625
-Well, you, not me.
-(laughs)

10:17.625 --> 10:19.750
I wait until after
the store closes.

10:22.375 --> 10:24.458
♪♪

10:24.458 --> 10:26.083
Merry Christmas, ladies.

10:26.083 --> 10:27.709
WOMEN:
Thanks, Chris.

10:27.709 --> 10:31.709
We are going to find this
bride-to-be's perfect dress.

10:31.709 --> 10:32.667
(women exclaiming)

10:32.667 --> 10:35.667
Whoever cries first wins!

10:35.667 --> 10:37.333
This is going to be
so fun. Whee!

10:37.333 --> 10:39.792
Honey, I know your mom
couldn't be here,

10:39.792 --> 10:42.834
but don't worry,
I'll be your substitute mom,

10:42.834 --> 10:46.125
and I could even pretend things
are complicated between us.

10:46.125 --> 10:48.667
Anything, just to make this
a special day for you.

10:48.667 --> 10:50.166
Thank you so much, Joan.

10:50.166 --> 10:51.750
Just don't run off
with Chris, okay?

10:51.750 --> 10:52.959
'Cause that's something
my real mom would do.

10:52.959 --> 10:54.041
Okay.

10:54.041 --> 10:55.125
JEN: I feel like
that's not an option.

10:55.125 --> 10:56.250
-You don't know her.
-Oh!

10:56.250 --> 10:57.792
JOAN: This day is
special for me, too,

10:57.792 --> 10:59.709
because I didn't get to do this
for Heather's wedding

10:59.709 --> 11:00.792
'cause she was pregnant,

11:00.792 --> 11:03.000
and Jen bought her dress in a
thrift store because she's edgy.

11:03.000 --> 11:04.583
JEN:
Yeah, hey, quick tip.

11:04.583 --> 11:06.125
Go for the couture dresses first

11:06.125 --> 11:07.959
so they start pouring
the good bubbly.

11:07.959 --> 11:09.166
And then at the last minute,

11:09.166 --> 11:10.625
you go over and get
a knock-off dress,

11:10.625 --> 11:12.625
because the champagne is already
in our stomachs,

11:12.625 --> 11:14.667
so take that, bitches.
Mm, yeah.

11:14.667 --> 11:16.125
Let's try on some dresses.

11:16.125 --> 11:17.083
(women exclaim)

11:17.083 --> 11:19.083
Well, you, not me.

11:19.083 --> 11:20.792
I wait until after
the store closes.

11:20.792 --> 11:21.709
(laughter)

11:21.709 --> 11:23.417
-Come on.
-Yes, diva, yes!

11:23.417 --> 11:25.625
Chris, honey, running
on empty over here.

11:25.625 --> 11:26.709
Thank you.

11:26.709 --> 11:29.625
So, what do we think?

11:29.625 --> 11:32.250
That looks fun to dance in.

11:32.250 --> 11:33.625
JEN:
Yeah, it's...

11:33.625 --> 11:35.000
I'm almost at a loss for words.

11:35.000 --> 11:36.458
Joan, I'm going to
pass the mic to you.

11:36.458 --> 11:37.417
Terrible.

11:38.417 --> 11:39.333
Oh, my...

11:39.333 --> 11:40.542
Oh, I didn't
mean that, honey.

11:40.542 --> 11:42.625
-It just popped out.
-It's fine!

11:42.625 --> 11:44.041
You are beautiful.

11:44.041 --> 11:45.875
Cut me off;
it's the champagne.

11:45.875 --> 11:47.834
COLLEEN: No, I'm not crazy
about this dress, either.

11:47.834 --> 11:50.166
It's just, Chris wanted me
to channel my inner Chris.

11:50.166 --> 11:52.750
Oh, don't do that
to her, ever.

11:52.750 --> 11:54.625
Oh, oh, no, sure--
you know what?

11:54.625 --> 11:56.041
I have some princess necklines

11:56.041 --> 11:57.875
and some cap sleeves.

11:57.875 --> 11:59.542
My middle name is options.

11:59.542 --> 12:00.625
-Oh.
-(chuckles)

12:00.625 --> 12:02.208
Isn't this so fun?

12:02.208 --> 12:03.750
-So fun!
-Super fun!

12:03.750 --> 12:05.458
(singsongy):
Options!

12:05.458 --> 12:06.542
(chuckles)

12:07.625 --> 12:09.458
Anyone else sick of Chris?

12:09.458 --> 12:11.834
What about...this one?

12:11.834 --> 12:13.667
Tavern hussy.

12:13.667 --> 12:14.625
Oh, my gosh!

12:14.625 --> 12:16.208
Oh, I'm so sorry.

12:16.208 --> 12:18.417
It's okay. It's an upgrade
from pirate wench.

12:18.417 --> 12:20.542
(chuckles) There's more
where this came from.

12:21.875 --> 12:23.208
I don't mean to be dramatic,

12:23.208 --> 12:25.542
because that seems to be
Chris's thing,

12:25.542 --> 12:29.417
but have we been here for
1,001 black, moonless nights?

12:29.417 --> 12:30.875
Yeah, maybe even longer.

12:30.875 --> 12:32.834
But you know what,
if you want to get out of here,

12:32.834 --> 12:34.959
all you have to do is,
next time she comes out,

12:34.959 --> 12:37.250
tell her you love it,
and then we can skedaddle.

12:37.250 --> 12:38.542
I don't know, this seems

12:38.542 --> 12:40.709
like such an important thing
to lie about.

12:40.709 --> 12:42.959
No, come on,
just make something up.

12:42.959 --> 12:44.583
Here, try it out on me.

12:44.583 --> 12:46.834
Jen, I love how you...

12:46.834 --> 12:48.333
You know what?
I'm regretting this already.

12:48.333 --> 12:49.417
Okay, but I have a good one

12:49.417 --> 12:51.000
for the next time
you wear that outfit.

12:51.000 --> 12:52.083
Okay, so when she comes out,

12:52.083 --> 12:53.667
you just tell her
that it looks beautiful.

12:53.667 --> 12:55.291
Oh, I need some more champagne

12:55.291 --> 12:57.000
if I'm going to lie like this.

12:57.000 --> 12:59.500
I heard the "C" word!

12:59.500 --> 13:01.375
What about this one?

13:01.375 --> 13:02.875
Boo!

13:02.875 --> 13:05.291
Okay, I'm going
to keep trying, okay.

13:06.375 --> 13:07.500
Joan?

13:07.500 --> 13:09.333
Well, I just can't bear
the thought of her

13:09.333 --> 13:12.625
walking down the aisle in a
dress that's less than perfect.

13:12.625 --> 13:15.834
Hey, guys,
check this out. Huh?

13:15.834 --> 13:18.792
This is the dress
I totally would have worn

13:18.792 --> 13:21.959
when I got married
had I not been knocked up.

13:21.959 --> 13:23.959
I think dressing like that
is what got you knocked up.

13:23.959 --> 13:25.417
Do you think that Colleen
would mind

13:25.417 --> 13:26.750
if I wore this to the wedding?

13:26.750 --> 13:28.875
I mean, of course she wouldn't
mind. Why would she mind?

13:28.875 --> 13:29.875
I'm going to wear it,

13:29.875 --> 13:31.125
but let's keep it

13:31.125 --> 13:33.250
as, like, a fun surprise,
so don't tell her.

13:33.250 --> 13:35.375
(sighs)

13:35.375 --> 13:37.083
Hey, how's it
going in here?

13:37.083 --> 13:39.709
Pretty good. I think the next
one's going to do the trick.

13:39.709 --> 13:42.000
Okay, um, listen,

13:42.000 --> 13:43.583
Joan is feeling
a lot of pressure

13:43.583 --> 13:45.583
to make sure that you find
the perfect dress,

13:45.583 --> 13:48.208
and you should really just
choose the one you want.

13:48.208 --> 13:49.875
You know, the one
that makes you happy,

13:49.875 --> 13:52.667
or really any dress, because
this is a living nightmare.

13:52.667 --> 13:53.917
I already picked a dress.

13:53.917 --> 13:55.125
What?

13:55.125 --> 13:56.500
I want to wear my dream dress.

13:56.500 --> 13:59.208
The dress I bought
the first time I was engaged.

13:59.208 --> 14:01.417
But then I found out
that this day of shopping

14:01.417 --> 14:03.291
meant so much to Joan.

14:03.291 --> 14:07.125
Okay, so we've, we've been
here all day for nothing.

14:07.125 --> 14:08.041
Yeah.

14:08.041 --> 14:09.291
-Okay.
-I'm sorry.

14:09.291 --> 14:11.000
I just thought I was being
so thoughtful

14:11.000 --> 14:12.709
because I wanted this
to be the day

14:12.709 --> 14:14.083
that she never had with Heather.

14:14.083 --> 14:16.083
Well, that is very sweet.

14:16.083 --> 14:17.542
-I thought so.
JEN: Yeah.

14:17.542 --> 14:19.583
But seriously, don't ever
pull this crap with me again.

14:19.583 --> 14:20.959
I got a sitter for this.

14:20.959 --> 14:24.500
♪♪

14:24.500 --> 14:26.041
Oh, Chris, thank you so much

14:26.041 --> 14:28.458
for helping me find
the dress of my dreams.

14:28.458 --> 14:30.625
Oh, my wife wore something
like that at our wedding.

14:30.625 --> 14:32.917
-Oh.
-Confused?

14:32.917 --> 14:33.917
So was I.

14:35.333 --> 14:37.417
-It's so pretty.
-Oh, thank you.

14:37.417 --> 14:38.500
But you know it's not
a dress, right?

14:38.500 --> 14:39.500
It's bridal lingerie.

14:39.500 --> 14:41.792
Please don't ruin
my special day.

14:41.792 --> 14:45.542
♪♪

14:45.542 --> 14:47.291
(whispers): Clementine's
been coming on to me.

14:47.291 --> 14:48.750
Clementine who?

14:48.750 --> 14:50.333
Tyler's wife.

14:50.333 --> 14:52.250
(both laughing)

14:55.625 --> 14:59.625
♪♪

14:59.625 --> 15:01.583
Heather, someone ate
my secret Pop-Tarts

15:01.583 --> 15:03.125
I had hidden behind
the rice cakes.

15:03.125 --> 15:04.333
I know they were there.

15:04.333 --> 15:06.417
I was thinking about them
all day and now they're gone.

15:06.417 --> 15:07.750
(gasps)
And my secret Reese's Cups

15:07.750 --> 15:10.417
that were hidden
behind the kale chips!

15:10.417 --> 15:12.792
Well, I'm sure somebody
got hungry and ate them.

15:12.792 --> 15:14.750
You know, there's more people
in the house now.

15:14.750 --> 15:16.083
Too many people in this house.

15:16.083 --> 15:17.542
When I look
under that treadmill,

15:17.542 --> 15:19.792
there better be a box
of Krispy Kremes.

15:19.792 --> 15:21.875
I don't think your dad
wants me living here.

15:21.875 --> 15:22.875
What makes you say that?

15:22.875 --> 15:24.375
I overheard him saying

15:24.375 --> 15:25.625
there's too many people
in the house.

15:25.625 --> 15:27.250
I'm the too many people.

15:27.250 --> 15:29.291
Or maybe he's mad
we're freeloading.

15:29.291 --> 15:30.583
Which we are.

15:30.583 --> 15:32.625
And if we want to keep
freeloading, which we do,

15:32.625 --> 15:34.917
we should go out of our way
to be extra nice to him.

15:34.917 --> 15:36.917
Okay, I could do that.

15:36.917 --> 15:43.208
♪♪

15:43.208 --> 15:44.750
What are you doing?

15:44.750 --> 15:46.625
-Hmm?
-Let me do that.

15:46.625 --> 15:48.458
No, you don't...

15:48.458 --> 15:49.834
Hey, that's my sponge mitt.

15:49.834 --> 15:51.208
You just sit there
and watch,

15:51.208 --> 15:52.834
and tell me if I miss a spot.

15:56.458 --> 15:57.542
Sit!

15:57.542 --> 16:04.458
♪♪

16:05.750 --> 16:09.166
Heather! Heather?

16:09.166 --> 16:10.667
CLEMENTINE:
Hey.

16:10.667 --> 16:12.333
They all went out.

16:12.333 --> 16:13.667
It's just you and me.

16:13.667 --> 16:14.834
It's okay.

16:14.834 --> 16:16.625
I won't let you get lonely.

16:16.625 --> 16:18.458
Should I put on a show for you?

16:18.458 --> 16:20.291
What?

16:20.291 --> 16:22.041
No, I don't think
that'd be appropriate.

16:22.041 --> 16:23.750
Don't worry,
I know what you like.

16:23.750 --> 16:25.041
No, you don't.

16:25.041 --> 16:27.583
♪♪

16:27.583 --> 16:29.542
CLEMENTINE:
<i>When Sharks Attack, </i>right?

16:29.542 --> 16:30.959
♪♪

16:35.500 --> 16:36.917
(giggling)

16:36.917 --> 16:37.875
Oh, man.

16:37.875 --> 16:39.959
Things are about to get weird.

16:39.959 --> 16:41.041
-Yeah?
-Listen, Heather,

16:41.041 --> 16:42.125
I think it's time you knew

16:42.125 --> 16:43.750
that Clementine's
been hitting on me.

16:43.750 --> 16:44.792
Clementine who?

16:44.792 --> 16:45.959
Our daughter-in-law.

16:45.959 --> 16:47.500
I was hoping
it would just pass,

16:47.500 --> 16:49.083
but she keeps sending me
these signals.

16:49.083 --> 16:50.583
Yeah, like the barista
sends you signals,

16:50.583 --> 16:52.500
like when she puts
a heart in your foam?

16:52.500 --> 16:54.125
Hey, they don't do that
for everybody.

16:54.125 --> 16:55.125
Some people just get a dollop.

16:55.125 --> 16:56.166
Mm-hmm, yeah, listen.

16:56.166 --> 16:57.667
Honey, I'm so glad
that you told me this

16:57.667 --> 16:59.834
because I can go talk to Jen

16:59.834 --> 17:01.917
about filing a restraining order
against Clementine.

17:01.917 --> 17:03.333
No, you shouldn't have
to live like that.

17:03.333 --> 17:04.333
I mean, just in case,
let's...

17:04.333 --> 17:06.542
-Just in case what?
-Oh, Tim's going to tell you.

17:06.542 --> 17:08.667
Christmas is about to
come early for you guys.

17:09.834 --> 17:12.166
What's going on?

17:12.166 --> 17:14.375
This is going to sound
crazy, but, um...

17:14.375 --> 17:16.542
(whispers): Clementine's
been coming on to me.

17:16.542 --> 17:17.959
Clementine who?

17:17.959 --> 17:19.542
Tyler's wife.

17:19.542 --> 17:22.333
(both laughing)

17:22.333 --> 17:24.750
Yes, I thought it was a little
unbelievable myself, at first,

17:24.750 --> 17:26.542
but it's really happening.

17:26.542 --> 17:28.417
So when she comes out here,
you tell me if I'm wrong.

17:28.417 --> 17:29.667
Oh, I could just
tell you right now.

17:29.667 --> 17:30.667
You're wrong.

17:30.667 --> 17:36.583
♪♪

17:38.083 --> 17:39.542
(sighs)
I hope this does the trick.

17:39.542 --> 17:40.875
Guacamole is my dad's
favorite.

17:40.875 --> 17:42.125
He eats it like pudding.

17:42.125 --> 17:44.250
I wish he didn't like it
so spicy.

17:44.250 --> 17:46.208
I got some of this habañero
juice on my lips

17:46.208 --> 17:48.083
and now they're burning
like hell.

17:48.083 --> 17:50.542
Oh, let me help
get that off you.

17:53.000 --> 17:54.750
Ow. (clears throat)

17:54.750 --> 17:57.208
That's really hot.

17:57.208 --> 17:58.208
Mom?

17:58.208 --> 17:59.166
What, what, what?

17:59.166 --> 18:01.500
-What's the matter?
-(gasps)

18:01.500 --> 18:03.500
TIM: The only explanation
I can come up with

18:03.500 --> 18:05.083
is that she likes dad bod.

18:05.083 --> 18:06.625
I read about it;
it's a real thing.

18:06.625 --> 18:08.250
There's just some women
who go crazy

18:08.250 --> 18:10.667
for a man shaped like
a sturdy sack of flour.

18:10.667 --> 18:12.625
That's why I'm thankful
every day I'm so shredded.

18:12.625 --> 18:14.834
All right, guys,
watch closely.

18:15.875 --> 18:17.917
So...

18:17.917 --> 18:20.041
I know guacamole's
your favorite.

18:20.041 --> 18:22.250
Not today,
I'm trying to cut back.

18:22.250 --> 18:23.250
Oh, come on.

18:23.250 --> 18:24.625
You deserve it.

18:24.625 --> 18:26.250
Be a little naughty.

18:26.250 --> 18:28.792
It's okay to cheat.

18:28.792 --> 18:30.542
I'm not interested.

18:32.583 --> 18:34.375
What do I have to do?

18:36.417 --> 18:37.709
Oh, my God,
you're right.

18:39.542 --> 18:41.417
Dad bod is real.

18:41.417 --> 18:43.834
I'm going to let myself go.

18:43.834 --> 18:46.083
Ah! You're there.

18:46.083 --> 18:47.667
What are you going to do?

18:47.667 --> 18:50.625
I just won't go
anywhere near Clementine.

18:50.625 --> 18:51.875
You think that's a good plan?

18:53.083 --> 18:55.542
(indistinct chatter)

18:55.542 --> 18:58.333
♪♪

19:04.000 --> 19:05.000
Oh, thank you so much.

19:06.375 --> 19:07.583
Tim.

19:10.375 --> 19:12.458
Here, I saved you a chair.

19:12.458 --> 19:15.250
It's a little tight,
but I like it cozy.

19:15.250 --> 19:17.000
Okay, thanks.

19:17.000 --> 19:18.208
Heather.

19:18.208 --> 19:19.250
(whispers):
Heather!

19:21.917 --> 19:24.667
I asked Heather for
permission to do this, so...

19:24.667 --> 19:26.625
I hope it's okay.

19:28.041 --> 19:29.542
This can't happen.

19:30.250 --> 19:31.500
Why not?

19:31.500 --> 19:34.709
Because it's not right.
I'm sorry.

19:34.709 --> 19:37.000
It's not right that
I want to say grace?

19:37.000 --> 19:38.959
-Ooh, grace.
-Huh?

19:42.792 --> 19:45.000
Oh...(chuckles)

19:45.000 --> 19:46.875
JOAN: Why don't you want her
to say grace?

19:46.875 --> 19:48.041
Dad, this has
got to stop.

19:48.041 --> 19:49.792
You already made Clementine
feel uncomfortable

19:49.792 --> 19:50.750
around the house.

19:50.750 --> 19:52.166
I make<i> her feel</i>
uncomfortable?

19:52.166 --> 19:53.709
Yes, and she's been
trying all week

19:53.709 --> 19:54.750
to be extra nice to you

19:54.750 --> 19:57.375
so you'll be cool with her
moving in with us.

19:57.375 --> 19:58.583
Oh.

19:58.583 --> 20:00.083
-Oh, that's...
HEATHER: Hey, honey,

20:00.083 --> 20:02.625
why don't you tell everybody
why it is

20:02.625 --> 20:05.333
you think that Clem's been being
so nice to you?

20:05.333 --> 20:06.250
(shushes)

20:06.250 --> 20:07.792
What is he talking about?

20:07.792 --> 20:09.291
(others murmur)

20:09.291 --> 20:11.250
Merry Christmas, everybody.

20:11.250 --> 20:13.625
♪♪ Silent night ♪♪

20:14.583 --> 20:18.291
♪♪ Holy night ♪♪

20:18.291 --> 20:22.250
♪♪ All is calm ♪♪

20:22.250 --> 20:25.792
♪♪ All is bright... ♪♪

20:26.750 --> 20:29.208
Maybe we should move out.

20:29.208 --> 20:32.709
♪♪ Round a virgin,
got in a fight ♪♪

20:32.709 --> 20:39.041
♪♪ Sleep in heavenly peace ♪♪

20:40.041 --> 20:40.959
Now one for Jen!

20:40.959 --> 20:43.917
♪♪ Dreidel, dreidel, dreidel,
da-da-da-da-da-da ♪♪

20:43.917 --> 20:50.834
♪♪
